# Version Management & Git Tags

## Version Workflow (MANDATORY)

Every code change MUST follow this sequence:

### 1. Update Version (`_version.py`)
```python
# _version.py
__version__ = "X.Y.Z"
```

**Increment Rules:**
- **MAJOR** (X): Breaking changes (UI redesigns, removed features, incompatible changes)
- **MINOR** (Y): New features (backward compatible enhancements, new options)
- **PATCH** (Z): Bug fixes (error corrections, performance tweaks, docs)

### 2. Update CHANGELOG.md

Move changes from `[Unreleased]` to versioned section:

```markdown
## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD

### Added
- New features

### Changed
- Modifications to existing features

### Fixed
- Bug fixes

### Deprecated
- Soon-to-be removed features

### Removed
- Deleted features

### Security
- Security fixes
```

### 3. Commit Changes
```bash
git add _version.py CHANGELOG.md [other-files]
git commit -m "chore: bump version to X.Y.Z"
```

### 4. Create Annotated Tag
```bash
git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z - see CHANGELOG.md"
```

### 5. Push Everything
```bash
git push origin <branch-name>
git push origin vX.Y.Z
```

## Quick Commands

```bash
# List all tags
git tag

# Show tag details
git show vX.Y.Z

# Delete tag (if mistake)
git tag -d vX.Y.Z                    # local
git push origin --delete vX.Y.Z      # remote

# View release history
git log --tags --simplify-by-decoration --pretty="format:%ci %d"

# Compare versions
git diff v1.0.0 v1.1.0

# Check what's deployed
git describe --tags
```

## Tag Naming Convention

- Format: `vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- Examples: `v1.0.0`, `v2.3.1`, `v10.15.2`
- Always prefix with `v`
- Always use annotated tags (`-a` flag)

## Version Display Locations

Version automatically appears in:
- GUI window title: "Abstract Renumber Tool v{VERSION}"
- GUI footer: "Version {VERSION}"
- Executable name: "AbstractRenumberTool-v{VERSION}.exe"

All import from `_version.py` (single source of truth)

## Pre-Release Checklist

- [ ] Version incremented in `_version.py`
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated with release notes
- [ ] All tests passing (`pytest`)
- [ ] Build tested (`python3 build/build.py`)
- [ ] Changes committed
- [ ] Annotated tag created
- [ ] Tag pushed to remote

## Emergency: Fix Wrong Tag

```bash
# Delete incorrect tag
git tag -d vX.Y.Z
git push origin --delete vX.Y.Z

# Create correct tag (specify commit if needed)
git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z" [commit-hash]
git push origin vX.Y.Z
```

